  "description": [
    "mtrlt of Charles Sumner whose dying exclamation was take esire of my Civil Right bill that the colored children wars not eoual to the white children of the nation The proposition contained in the resolution that the people did not want mixed schools was as much as to say to the Congress of the Nation that the colored people of Alabama spurned the rights offered to them His remarks were loudly applauded and cheered The grand orators of the occasion were Smith the carpetbagger and Welch of Selma They are perhaps the most culti vated of their race in the Southern States In the course of his elaborate but sophomorlo epeeah Welch said Any negro who votes the Democratic ticket tramples on the dearest rights of his race If you would nave a Democrat go with you offer him an office Do that and see how quick he will take off the Democratic coat and put on the Republican blouse If we had offices nough to divide out we should have no lack of converts But dont let them stay In office until they get rich If you do they will retrograde Feed the new converts well lr you dont"
